I'm overseeing the monitoring of a robotic system operating within a high-precision manufacturing facility, and it's vital to keep track of the environmental conditions for the robots. We have a set of sensors installed on our robot which include temperature, humidity, and proximity detectors. It is imperative that we gather the most recent sensor data to ensure the robot functions within safe environmental parameters. The robot's system provides a RESTful API for this purpose. Could you execute the function to access real-time data from these sensors? Use the following API endpoint: 'https://robotics-system.example.com/api/sensors' to pull the latest readings for temperature, humidity, and proximity sensors.

The expected JSON structure for the real-time sensor data is as follows:

```json
{
  "temperature": {
    "value": "current temperature reading in Celsius",
    "timestamp": "ISO 8601 timestamp of the reading"
  },
  "humidity": {
    "value": "current humidity reading in percentage",
    "timestamp": "ISO 8601 timestamp of the reading"
  },
  "proximity": {
    "value": "current proximity reading in centimeters",
    "timestamp": "ISO 8601 timestamp of the reading"
  }
}
```

Please retrieve the data and return it in the above format.
